Research results of students singing leading roles at the annual academic conference of Zhejiang University open the human brain - Xinhuanet
Washing hands with air, judging diseases with breath, and accurately searching for the source of haze Last night, at the opening ceremony of the 2016 annual academic conference of Zhejiang University, a series of academic achievements with large brain holes were commended.
The main researchers of these achievements are students, research covers the environment, machinery, energy, medical care, life sciences, humanities education and other fields, students from a curious idea to create a lot of high-end inventions with application value, some of which have won awards at home and abroad.
Biosensors: Your Home Medical Examiner
The team of Zhang Diming, a doctoral student in the School of Biomedical Engineering, demonstrated a biosensor on the smartphone side, which is only half the size of a smartphone.
"All you need to do is breathe a little, and the instrument can initially detect your health from the composition of the gas you exhale."
According to Zhang, the sensor is connected to the smartphone, and after exhaling the gas, the health report will be displayed on the phone.
Smart wristbands on the market that can detect health generally detect physical parameters such as temperature and pulse.
The biosensor uses a new material, graphene, which targets chemical elements, and its keen "sense of smell" allows it to more deeply and accurately reflect the state of health.
Smart operating lamp: high-energy eyes of doctors
In addition to smartphones, smart operating lights are also used in the operating room.
The invention won a silver medal at this year's 44th International Exhibition of Inventions in Geneva, Switzerland.
The team of Zhu Linjing and Shen Junfei, master students of the School of Optoelectronic Science and Engineering, opened a new idea in the defects of the traditional operating lamp, and invented the intelligent LED surgical shadow-less lamp.
"A lot of diseases early detection, resection is not in place, with doctors operating room lights."
For example, if doctors can't see all the tumor tissue in time during early cancer screening, the cancer cells will spread later, Shen said.
The intelligent operating lamp has four discs that adjust the spectrum to enhance the difference between different tissues in light.
During the operation, the doctor can adjust the size, brightness, spectrum, color uniformity and shadow-free rate of the spot at any time according to the needs of the operation and personal habits.
This kind of intelligent operating lamp has been tested in hospitals such as Shao Yifu Hospital affiliated to Zhejiang University School of Medicine and Children's Hospital affiliated to Zhejiang University School of Medicine, and has received good feedback.
Last October, the invention won the first prize in the National Challenge Cup.
Washing hands with air: water saving and cool
Ordinary people wash their hands with water, at most wipe some soap, squeeze some hand sanitizer, and Li Qizhang and other students have invented an "air hand washing device".
As long as we stand on the installed hand sanitizer, our weight compresses the air out.
"It's like a pump.
The compressed air forms a fluid at the faucet and binds to the water.
So we can wash our hands! "
The color reaction and bacterial residue experiment proved that the effect of hand washing by this method is the same as that of ordinary hand washing.
This device only needs to rely on our own gravity as a drive, not only to ensure the degree of washing, but also to save 90% of the water, the whole process is completely energy-free, energy-saving and environmental protection.
Last year, at the second Global Major Challenges Summit, the invention won the only gold medal among many of the world's top schools.
Chongqing Secondary Vocational School Pilot Modern Apprenticeship System Enrollment Is an Enterprise Associate Employee - Xinhuanet
Yesterday, the reporter learned from the Municipal Education Commission that from this year, the city will pilot the "modern apprenticeship system" talent training model in 60 secondary vocational schools, students receiving the pilot training at the same time have apprenticeship status, and after enrollment entry will be pre-recorded as unit employees by the pilot enterprises.
The Municipal Education Commission requires that the standardization of secondary vocational school enrollment and enterprise employment procedures, clear apprentices of secondary vocational school students and enterprise prospective employees dual identity, in accordance with the principle of two-way selection, apprentices, schools and enterprises signed a tripartite agreement, for apprentices who have reached the age of 16 years and not reached the age of 18 years, apprentices, guardians, schools and enterprises must sign an agreement by the four parties to determine the rights and interests of all parties and apprentices in the training of specific positions, teaching content, rights and interests protection.
Pilot schools are encouraged to adopt the form of modern apprenticeships and cooperative enterprises to jointly carry out pre-job training and transfer training for enterprise employees.
Pilot schools should reform the mode of personnel training.
Schools and enterprises jointly design talent training programs, and jointly formulate professional teaching standards, curriculum standards, post standards, enterprise master standards, quality control standards and corresponding implementation plans.
The pilot takes the training system as a pilot cycle, and the internship time of students in enterprises is determined according to the professional talent training program, and the internship in Dinggang is generally 6 months.
In enterprise practice should implement enterprise group management mode, according to the characteristics of different majors, a master can bring 2 to 5 apprentices to form a study group, to ensure that students master the skills required for each rotation position.
According to the arrangement, from 2016 to August 2019, the city identified 60 municipal modern apprenticeship system pilot in three batches, each pilot number of about 50 people, a total of about 3,000 students (apprentices).
In accordance with the principle of pilot before implementation, and gradually advancing from point to point, we will explore the establishment of a long-term mechanism of joint enrollment, joint training, and integrated education between schools and enterprises, so as to effectively enhance students' job skills and improve the employment rate and quality of employment of students.
